# Growth Frameworks

Guidelines for designing growth loops, running experiments, optimizing retention, and scaling growth.

## Growth Model Selection

| Model | Best For |
|-------|----------|
| Sales-Led (SLG) | Enterprise, high ACV, complex products |
| Marketing-Led (MLG) | Mid-market, moderate ACV, education-heavy |
| Product-Led (PLG) | Low ACV, self-serve, high volume |
| Community-Led (CLG) | Developer tools, platforms, niche markets |
| Partner-Led | Geographic expansion, regulated industries |

## Growth Loop Anatomy

Every loop has four parts:
- **Input**: What triggers the loop (signup, content creation, purchase)
- **Action**: What the user does (share, invite, create, integrate)
- **Output**: What the action creates (new users, content, data improvement)
- **Amplifier**: What accelerates it (incentives, network effects, algorithmic distribution)

