## Experimentation Program

- **Idea backlog**: Central repository from all teams
- **Prioritization**: ICE scoring (Impact, Confidence, Ease) weekly
- **Velocity target**: 2-3 experiments per sprint minimum
- **Documentation**: Every experiment logged with hypothesis, results, learnings
- **Review**: Weekly cross-functional experiment review

### ICE Scoring Guide

| Score | Impact | Confidence | Ease |
|-------|--------|-----------|------|
| 10 | Massive (>25%) | Proven in similar context | Ship today |
| 7-9 | Large (10-25%) | Strong evidence | 1-2 days |
| 4-6 | Moderate (5-10%) | Reasonable hypothesis | 1-2 weeks |
| 1-3 | Small (<5%) | Pure guess | Major effort |

## Scaling Checklist

| Milestone | Next Action |
|-----------|-------------|
| Channel shows positive ROI at <$5K/month | Increase budget 2-3x |
| ROI holds at 2-3x budget | Continue scaling, test creative variants |
| Diminishing returns at higher spend | Cap spend, find next channel |
| One complete loop cycle observed | Reduce friction, measure cycle time |
| Loop output exceeds input consistently | Invest in amplifiers, remove bottlenecks |

## Common Pitfalls

- **Premature optimization**: Validate the full loop first. Ensure the right people arrive and convert before optimizing any single step.
- **Growth hacking without strategy**: Design a sustainable loop first, then experiment to optimize each step.
- **Ignoring retention**: Measure net growth (new minus churned). Fix retention before pouring more into acquisition.
